<P>
ADVICE TO YOUNG COPS AS THEY START CAREERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re your recent piece about three young LAPD officers one year after their 
entry into the exciting -- sometimes shocking -- world of professional law 
enforcement ("Welcome to the Real World," May 19). Although I applaud zeal in 
any occupation, we can only hope that these highly trained and appropriately 
sensitive citizen warriors never have the misfortune of being present during an 
unusually difficult arrest (i.e. the Rodney King fiasco), or worse, attempt to 
make the arrest themselves in front of a video camera. 
</P>
<P>
 FRED ROMERO 
</P>
<P>
