<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; SCHOOL: SCHOLARSHIP NAMED FOR TEACHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A future Cornell University student will receive a scholarship named for Dean 
P. Schenker, a University High School teacher. 
</P>
<P>
 Schenker, who teaches honors and advanced placement English, was chosen by 
Christopher Goffard, a graduating senior at Cornell in Ithaca, N.Y., as the 
teacher who made the most significant contribution to his education. 
</P>
<P>
 The $4,000 scholarship, awarded over a four-year period in Schenker's name, 
will be given to a Hamilton High School student who attends Cornell. The award 
will be given to an incoming student from another Los Angeles city school if no 
one from Hamilton enrolls at Cornell. 
</P>
<P>
 Goffard, who was enrolled at Hamilton from 1988 to 1990, was named a Merrill 
Presidential Scholar at Cornell by his dean, based on his scholastic 
achievement and leadership ability. 
</P>
