<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ANGELES CITY HALL JOURNAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A summary of selected City Hall actions last week that affect the Westside. 
</P>
<P>
 CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
<P>
 * RECREATION CENTERS -- Approved an agreement between the Los Angeles Board of 
Recreation and Parks and the Los Angeles County Department of Parks and 
Recreation that will earmark $830,000 toward a new gymnasium at the Westchester 
Recreation Center, 7000 W. Manchester Blvd.The project is one of 10 throughout 
the county to be financed with money from the Los Angeles County 1992 Parks 
Act. 
</P>
<P>
 * GETTY HOUSE -- Authorized the Getty House Restoration Foundation to conduct 
fund-raising events and accept donations to help finance the remodeling and 
refurbishment of Getty House, the official residence of the mayor. Once 
restored, the Hancock Park house is to be used to host city receptions and 
other civic functions. Mayor Richard Riordan declined to make the house his 
residence upon his election last year. HOW THEY VOTED 
</P>
<P>
 * SEXUAL HARASSMENT -- Recommended that Los Angeles Police Chief Willie 
Williams institute several new policies regarding sexual harassment within his 
ranks. Among the recommendations was the establishment of an independent 
civilian unit to investigate complaints of sexual harassment and to develop a 
comprehensive policy concerning the problem. Current policies on the subject 
are limited to a few paragraphs scattered in sections of the department's 
training manual. Passed 13-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Voting yes: John Ferraro, Marvin Braude, Zev Yaroslavsky, Ruth Galanter, Mark 
Ridley-Thomas, Jackie Goldberg. 
</P>
<P>
 Absent: Nate Holden. MICHAEL KRIKORIAN 
</P>
