<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; OPEN HOUSE AT BUCKINGHAM PALACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Miss out on last year's tours of Buckingham Palace? Queen Elizabeth is giving 
you a second chance.The palace will be open from Aug. 7 through Oct. 2, when 
visitors will be able to see 18 rooms and part of the State Apartments. 
</P>
<P>
 Visiting hours are daily from 9:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m., with the last admission 
at 4:30 p.m. Admission is about $12 for adults, $6 for children under 17 and 
$8.25 for those age 60 and older. Tickets will go on sale daily at a booth in 
St. James Park, opposite the Palace. For a free information sheet on visiting 
the palace, contact the British Tourist Authority, (800) 462-2748. 
</P>
