<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO -- Textile design celebrating "Earth's Magical Kingdom" is showcased 
at the 14th annual Fabric Fantasies Festival, June 10-11. The juried fabric 
festival is 10 a.m.-5:30 p.m. both days in Bazaar del Mundo, Old Town San Diego 
State Historic Park. Featured: a marketplace of fabrics, trims, beads and 
books; art-to-wear fashion shows at 12:30 p.m. both days, and a talk by 
designer Laurel Burch at 3 p.m. Friday. Free. (619) 296-3161. 
</P>
<P>
 AVALON -- Get a taste of life before "talkies" at the annual Silent Film 
Benefit, June 11, in the Avalon Theatre. The 1925 silent classic "Phantom of 
the Opera" is screened at 2 p.m., with accompaniment by master organist Gaylord 
Carter. A reception follows. $7, general. Tickets are limited. To purchase with 
a credit card, call (310) 510-1520. 
</P>
<P>
 SANTA ROSA -- The 16th annual Health and Harmony Music and Arts Festival '94 
is 10 a.m.-7 p.m. June 11-12 at the Sonoma County Fairgrounds. Highlights 
include the Health and Environmental Exposition; concerts by Charlie 
Musselwhite, Jefferson Starship, Sukay and others, and kids' activities at the 
Rainbow Center for Children. $7, general; $5, seniors; $4, kids 6-12; free for 
kids under 6. (707) 575-9355. 
</P>
<P>
 ISLETON -- Louisiana-style revelry awaits at the Great Isleton Crawdad 
Festival, June 17-19 along Main Street. Spicy festivities include: Cajun music, 
a carnival, and, of course, booths with Cajun food and other cuisines. 10 
a.m.-9 p.m. Friday; 10 a.m.-midnight Saturday; 10 a.m.-8 p.m. Sunday. A 
five-mile run is at 8 a.m. Sunday; a parade is noon Sunday. (916) 777-5880. 
</P>
<P>
 HOLLISTER -- Handicrafts by more than 100 artisans await at the Arts, Crafts 
and Music Festival, June 25-26 at Casa de Fruta. 10 a.m.-6 p.m. both days in 
the Casa de Sweets Pavilion. Free. (408) 842-9316. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
