<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; NETWORK INSTALLS ATMS IN MOSCOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The MasterCard/CIRRUS network has installed its first ATMs in Russia at three 
locations in Moscow: the Central Telegraph Office near Red Square; the 
Novoarbatskiy department store, Noviy Arbat 13, and at the Moscow International 
Airport. The machines, which have instructions in English, are dispensing 
dollars now, but will switch to rubles later. By the end of 1994, plans call 
for six more ATMs in Moscow and two in St. Petersburg. 
</P>
