<P>
AIDING THE FIGHT AGAINST TUBERCULOSIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * It is unfortunate that at this time of scarce financial resources at every 
level of government we are seeing cases of (tuberculosis) up 44% in 1993 
compared to 1991. The cases of TB in the schools reflect what is occurring in 
Orange County as a whole. 
</P>
<P>
 Solutions aren't just the responsibility of the public health system but for 
all of us as a community to find ways to deal with the crisis. 
</P>
<P>
 June is Tuberculosis Awareness Month. We all need to know what we can do to 
fight the resurgence of this disease. 
</P>
<P>
 Call the American Lung Assn. ((714) 835-LUNG) if you are interested in working 
with a community coalition formed to help control this epidemic. 
</P>
<P>
 PEARL JEMISON-SMITH 
