<HEADLINE>
<P>
GANGS' PUSH FOR PEACE OFFERS LIFE LESSONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Thank you for publishing the good news inherent in "Gangs Make Sweeping 
Change" (May 19). The last line in the story is a quote from a neighbor who no 
longer feels terrorized, " 'Now the boys see me walking and they say 'hello' to 
me. . . . This is a good example for the rest of the gangs.'" 
</P>
<P>
 It is a great example for the rest of the gangs and for all of us. The Times 
Valley Edition would be doing all of its readers a favor if it followed the 
stories of these courageous youths who have decided to adopt a kinder, more 
compassionate lifestyle. Their brave decision to live peacefully while helping 
heal their community is front page news, and we would all benefit from learning 
of it everyday. 
</P>
<P>
 CHRIS RISELEY 
</P>
<P>
 North Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
