<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; CRASH VICTIM IDENTIFIED AS RETIRED 
ENGINEER, 83 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 83-year-old man who died after his car was broadsided by an armored truck 
just outside a Ventura cemetery has been identified by the Ventura County 
coroner's office as Howard Schaaf, a retired engineer from Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 Schaaf was exiting Ivy Lawn Memorial Park on Valentine Road after visiting his 
wife's grave when he was struck by the truck operated by Armored Transport of 
Ventura, a Ventura Police Department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Schaaf died instantly, according to Deputy Coroner Mitch Breese. The driver of 
the truck was traveling within the speed limit and not considered at fault, the 
police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The armored truck driver and the two guards who rode with him were uninjured 
in the incident, the police spokesman said. The three remained in the vehicle 
until another armored truck arrived to remove the money it had collected from 
banks and markets in Ventura. SCOTT HADLY 
