WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; GIRL CRITICAL IN 65-FOOT FALL FROM CASCADES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 14-year-old girl was critically injured Saturday morning after falling 65 
feet from lower Rose Valley Falls north of Ojai, a Fire Department spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, whose name was not released by authorities, had climbed up to a 
ledge at the lower falls about 8:30 a.m. She slipped on moss while taking in 
the view, said Ventura County Fire Capt. Bob Myers from Station 22 in Meiners 
Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 Myers said the girl fell into a six-inch pool of water, striking several 
jagged rocks when she hit. She suffered cuts and scrapes to her head, internal 
injuries and possibly a broken leg, he said.  
</P>
<P>
 The girl was taken by Sheriff's Department helicopter to the Ventura County 
Medical Center, where she is listed in critical but stable condition, a Medical 
Center spokeswoman said. SCOTT HADLY 
