<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTH: SOUTH; EXCHANGE STUDENTS TO VISIT BRAZIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cultural Education Project of Teen Post Inc. is accepting applications for 
9- to 17-year-olds interested in a cultural exchange visit to Brazil. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-week trip is scheduled for August and will include visits to Rio de 
Janeiro and Bahia. Cost for airfare and hotel is $1,277 per person for double 
occupancy, and $1,225 for triple occupancy. 
</P>
<P>
 Periodic fund-raisers have been held to offset some of the costs for youths, 
said Georgia Hunt, program liaison coordinator for Teen Post, a nonprofit 
program funded by the Los Angeles Community Development Department. Adults will 
be required to pay full fare.  
</P>
