<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: WESTLAKE; DOWNTOWN YMCA GETS $100,000 GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Amateur Athletic Foundation recently awarded a $100,035 grant to the 
Ketchum/Downtown YMCA for sports equipment, new lighting and other costs for an 
athletic field scheduled to be completed this summer at 3rd Street and Lucas 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The YMCA will transform the vacant lot into a soccer field and supervise 
recreation programs there. The grant is part of a $1-million fund the 
foundation established in July, 1992, to finance youth sports programs in areas 
affected by the riots.  
</P>
<P>
 The foundation, a legacy of the 1984 Summer Olympics in Los Angeles, awards 
grants to youth sports organizations, initiates its own youth sports programs 
and manages the Paul Ziffren Sports Resource Center Library. 
</P>
</TEXT>
