<HEADLINE>
<P>
APPLICATIONS BEING ACCEPTED FOR JOBS PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 El Centro del Pueblo is recruiting young adults from Pico-Union, 
Temple-Beaudry, Echo Park, Silver Lake and parts of Hollywood for its annual 
job training program. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit organization is accepting applications for the Job Training 
Partnership Act Youth Employment Competency program, primarily from people ages 
18 to 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Participants will complete a 36-hour workshop before being placed in clerical, 
cashier or stockroom jobs. Wages range from $4.87 to $5.35 an hour for 30 to 40 
hours a week. 
</P>
<P>
 El Centro del Pueblo is also seeking additional employers to provide training 
work sites; the organization will pay the wages and fringe benefits for all 
program participants. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is free and sponsored by the city's Community Development 
Department and the Private Industry Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 483-6335. 
