FATHER OF SEPARATED TWINS HELD IN CAR THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The father of Siamese twins separated last summer is back behind bars, facing 
an auto theft charge less than two months after his release from prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Kenneth Lakeberg, 27, was being held without bond Saturday. He is accused of 
stealing a friend's car. Lakeberg spent six months in prison after skipping a 
parole hearing in October. 
</P>
<P>
 He also admitted buying cocaine with about $1,300 of the money donated for his 
daughters' medical bills. 
</P>
<P>
 His wife, Reitha, gave birth to conjoined twins on June 29, 1993. Amy and 
Angela Lakeberg were separated in August. Amy died and Angela remains in 
serious but stable condition. 
</P>
