<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Hezbollah guerrillas were killed in clashes with Israel's surrogate army 
in southern Lebanon, keeping tensions high Saturday in the wake of an Israeli 
air raid on a training camp used by the militant Islamic group. 
</P>
<P>
 But there were no reports of new rocket attacks on northern Israel after two 
days of such strikes in retaliation for Thursday's air raid, which killed as 
many as 50 people. 
</P>
