<P>
HUNGARY'S SOCIALISTS CHOOSE PREMIER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gyula Horn, Hungary's last Communist foreign minister, was chosen on Saturday 
by his winning Socialist Party to be the new prime minister. 
</P>
<P>
 Horn and his government must be confirmed by Parliament. But his Socialists, a 
reform wing of the former Communists, won a majority in last month's elections, 
virtually ensuring that he will be the new head of government. 
</P>
<P>
 The 62-year-old Horn has vowed to continue Hungary's transition to a market 
economy, and on Saturday he reiterated his desire to have a coalition 
government. 
