WORLD CUP '94 / DAILY REPORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL DWYRE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Midfielder John Harkes, who arrived recently from England but has yet to play 
a game with the U.S. team, said at halftime he was worried that the U.S. 
backline was appearing somewhat vulnerable. 
</P>
<P>
 "The way we are standing flat," he said, "I fear that one ball over the top 
will get us." 
</P>
<P>
 Harkes, who said he didn't expect any problems fitting in with the team after 
a few more practices, was asked what had been the most surprising thing he had 
noticed about the U.S. team upon his arrival. 
</P>
<P>
 "Alexi Lalas' beard," he said. BILL DWYRE 
