<HEADLINE>
<P>
KIRBY WINS MAIN EVENT AS THREE RECORDS ARE SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Kirby, the defending Sprint Car Racing Assn. champion, won his second 
main event and his second trophy dash Saturday at Ventura Raceway on a night 
when three track records fell. 
</P>
<P>
 The 29-year-old Lomita resident took more than a second off the three-lap 
record in the trophy dash, finishing in 36.18 seconds.He then won a decisive 
victory in the 30-lap feature. 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Shuman, who set a single-lap qualifying record of 11.803 seconds, held the 
previous three-lap record of 37.41. Gary Howard of Rancho Cucamonga held the 
qualifying mark at 12.006. 
</P>
<P>
 Kirby inherited the lead on the sixth lap of the main event, after hometown 
favorite Cory Kruseman hit the first-turn wall while being challenged by Kirby. 
</P>
<P>
 Rip Williams of Yorba Linda, who established a 10-lap record of 2:01.7 while 
winning the first heat race, finished second. Jerry Meyer of Chino was third. 
</P>
<P>
 Shuman dropped out on Lap 22 while running third. He finished 14 overall. 
</P>
