<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONDO COLUMNIST HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Condo Q&A" columnist Jan Hickenbottom has been honored by the Community 
Assns.Institute for her columns written in response to readers' questions about 
quake-related problems after the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 "Always offering common-sense solutions, Jan's columns were an invaluable 
source of information for community associations and their homeowners who were 
struggling with monumental problems," said CAI secretary Sue Dyckmans, in 
presenting an award to Hickenbottom at the group's recent national convention 
in San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
 Hickenbottom began writing the "Condo Q&A" column more than four years ago. An 
active CAI volunteer, she has worked in the community association management 
industry for 15 years. She now runs her own consulting business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA060594-0388 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 048737 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 5, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
