ARCHITECTS FEATURED AT MOCA PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Architecture and the New Muse: Design, Materials and Technology Shaping 
Recent Cultural Facilities" will be presented June 17, 9 a.m. to 1 p.m., at the 
Los Angeles Museum of Contemporary Art (MOCA). 
</P>
<P>
 Moderated by Richard Keating, the program will feature architects Moshe 
Safdie, Norman Pfeiffer, Barton Myers, Michael Hallmark, Richard Kuhn and Doss 
Mabe. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $50 for USC Architectural Guild members, $55 for the general 
public and $30 for students. More details are available from the USC 
Architectural Guild, (213) 740-4471. 
</P>
