<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREEN THUMB; GLIDE INTO SOME RELAXATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLINGSON, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Glide into some well-deserved rest and relaxation on your patio, porch or 
lawn. There is little that helps relieve tension and stress after a long day 
like the gentle back-and-forth motion of a patio glider.Glider swings have long 
been a part of the American "relaxation" scene, and one sitting can take a 
person back to the days of big front porches and band concerts in the park. 
</P>
<P>
 Measuring 51 inches long and built to last, this version is made from Douglas 
fir and plywood. However, one can easily substitute redwood for the fir to give 
a more rustic look. A detailed step-by-step plan features more than a dozen 
photos, along with drawings, instructions and handy finishing tips. The gliding 
assembly is simple and will give years of trouble-free operation. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information on today's project, call (800) 828-2453.  
</P>
