GARDENER'S CHECKLIST: GREEN THUMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Use wire cylinders to keep tomato plants off the ground, prevent rot, 
improve fruit set and ease harvest. 
</P>
<P>
 * Soaker hoses and drip irrigation systems are both excellent additions to 
your garden. Both help cut back on water usage. 
